commit.message:
https: disable_ssl_certificate_validation caused ValueError: Cannot set verify_mode to CERT_NONE when check_hostname is enabled

In CPython < 3.7 SSLContext required different order of setting attributes check_hostname and verify_mode in enable/disable scenarios.

https://bugs.python.org/issue31431
https://github.com/httplib2/httplib2/pull/231

Signed-off-by: tomasz.ziolkowski <tomasz.ziolkowski@allegro.pl>
Co-authored-by: Sergey Shepelev <temotor@gmail.com>

commit.message:
Fix parsing http_proxy environment.

Parsing proxy was breaking when proxy URL was set to ipv6 address. There
was also weird handling of proxy without a password. We should rely on
parsing those fields in urllib which is present in all supported
versions.
Align comment quotes to conform to the style of the file and help certain IDEs to understand the code

commit.message:
proxy: correct extraction of errno from pysocks ProxyConnectionError

Fixes `IndexError: tuple index out of range` trying to extract `errno` from `ProxyConnectionError` from pysocks package, because that exception class lacks `args` attribute.

https://github.com/httplib2/httplib2/issues/170
https://github.com/httplib2/httplib2/pull/202

verification.payload:
tree 1ca25e1d641256aa51260435f0026699633b3ddb
